      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DEVILISH SUN (1) was close to breaking through last time in work, closing the prep as favourite and finishing second at Dubbo before a four month break. Jumps from a wide alley but is ready for a bold run while fresh. FLYING MOLLY (6) went forward and gave a great sight before finishing second when resuming last time out over 1000m at Muswellbrook. Has her share of ability and will prove hard to beat in this suitable race. JACK THE BOSS (2) finished second last time over 1000m at Binnaway, beaten 2 lengths. Meeting a tougher field but on his best form he is capable of a big performance. ALBERT'S PICK (5) resumes from a spell of four-and-a-half months. Looked close to a win before that break, finishing off with a minor placing over 1300m at Armidale. Has ability and must be included in calculations.",
